Vice President Kamala Harris and President Joe Biden spoke at an event in the East Room of the White House to celebrate the 11th anniversary of the signing of the Affordable Care Act (ACA). They highlighted the success of the ACA in providing affordable healthcare to millions of Americans and called for further action to expand coverage and lower costs. Vice President Harris emphasized the importance of allowing Medicare to directly negotiate prescription drug prices with pharmaceutical companies and making the ACA subsidies permanent. President Biden signed an executive order to strengthen and expand access to healthcare coverage. He also spoke about the need to continue building on the ACA and criticized Republican efforts to repeal the law.